# User docs sync

When changing behavior users see (CLI flags, keys, `:` commands, search, status bar, exit codes), update **all** relevant user-facing docs in the same change:

| Artifact | Role |
|----------|------|
| `docs/tutorial.md` | Getting-started guide: workflows, examples, tips |
| `man/csvi.1` | Installed manual (`man csvi`): OPTIONS, KEYS, COMMANDS, EXIT STATUS |
| `Commands.md` | Authoritative key/command reference and migration table |
| `README.md` | Install, one-line usage, links to tutorial and Commands |

Also update `docs/architecture.md` CLI/exit-code tables when flags or exit codes change (see `cli-surface-sync.mdc`).

## What triggers an update

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| New/changed CLI flag | `main.c`, `man/csvi.1`, `docs/tutorial.md`, `Commands.md`, `README.md`, `docs/architecture.md` |
| New/changed key binding | `Commands.md`, `man/csvi.1`, `docs/tutorial.md` |
| New/changed `:` command | `Commands.md`, `man/csvi.1`, `docs/tutorial.md` |
| Exit code change | `errors.h`, `man/csvi.1`, `docs/tutorial.md`, `docs/architecture.md` |
| User-visible workflow (search, header, grid) | `docs/tutorial.md`; reference tables in `Commands.md` / `man/csvi.1` if surface changed |

## Consistency

- **1-based** row/column numbers everywhere in user docs.
- Default separator is `;` unless code defaults change.
- Keep `Commands.md` and `man/csvi.1` aligned; `docs/tutorial.md` may use prose and examples but must not contradict them.
- Do not add CLI flags or commands without updating `man/csvi.1` and `docs/tutorial.md`.
